From: Markus Fritsche <mfritsche@localhost>
Date: Tue, 24 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] alsa: ucm2: Rockchip/rk3588-es8316: add Speaker output device

The HiFi use-case profile for the RK3588 ES8316 codec previously defined
only a Headphones output device (backed by the hp-det-gpios jack) and a
Headset capture device.  Because the Headphones device carries a
JackControl, its availability tracks the physical jack state: when no
headphones are inserted the port is reported as "not available", which
causes the entire HiFi profile to become unavailable.  PipeWire/
WirePlumber therefore falls back to the low-priority "pro-audio" profile,
producing a single undifferentiated "Built-in Audio Pro" sink with no
speaker or headphone sub-devices visible to the user.

Add a Speaker SectionDevice without a JackControl so the device is always
available and the HiFi profile remains selectable even without headphones.
Add JackHWMute "Headphones" so that PipeWire routes audio away from the
Speaker sink when headphones are inserted; the resulting absence of an
active PCM consumer causes the kernel-side DAPM "Amplifier" output-driver
widget to power down, driving the speaker-amplifier enable GPIO (GPIO1_A6)
low and muting the speakers automatically.

The EnableSequence / DisableSequence of the Speaker device use the same
Playback Polarity control as the Headphones device: Normal during playback,
R Invert when disabled (which acoustic-cancels any residual cross-feed to a
shared speaker line).  PlaybackPriority is set lower than Headphones (100
vs 200) so that when headphones are available they are preferred by
WirePlumber's automatic port selection.

Generated-by: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Signed-off-by: Markus Fritsche <mfritsche@localhost>
---
 Rockchip/rk3588-es8316/HiFi.conf | 19 +++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 19 insertions(+)

--- a/Rockchip/rk3588-es8316/HiFi.conf
+++ b/Rockchip/rk3588-es8316/HiFi.conf
@@ -1,2 +1,21 @@
+SectionDevice."Speaker" {
+	Comment "Built-in Speakers"
+
+	EnableSequence [
+		cset "name='Playback Polarity' 'Normal'"
+	]
+
+	DisableSequence [
+		cset "name='Playback Polarity' 'R Invert'"
+	]
+
+	Value {
+		PlaybackPriority 100
+		PlaybackPCM "hw:${CardId}"
+		PlaybackMixerElem "Headphone Mixer"
+		PlaybackMasterElem "DAC"
+		JackHWMute "Headphones"
+	}
+}
+
 SectionDevice."Headphones" {
 	Comment "Headphones"
